1
00:00:09,990 --> 00:00:13,390
[Jeon Hye Jin]

2
00:00:13,390 --> 00:00:16,730
[Choi Soo Young]

3
00:00:21,990 --> 00:00:23,690
[Ahn Jae Wook]

4
00:00:23,690 --> 00:00:26,590
[Park Sung Hoon]

5
00:00:35,790 --> 00:00:39,290
[Not Others]

6
00:00:39,290 --> 00:00:44,440
[This drama is fictitious. The characters, organizations, locales, incidents, and circumstances featured have no relevance to real life.]

7
00:00:49,030 --> 00:00:51,950
Ouch! I said it hurts!

8
00:00:51,950 --> 00:00:56,240
Geez, who did you get your coarse hair from?

9
00:00:56,240 --> 00:00:58,850
Who else could it be? I resemble you.

10
00:00:58,850 --> 00:01:01,510
That makes no sense.

11
00:01:01,510 --> 00:01:04,570
How could this hair resemble yours?

12
00:01:06,250 --> 00:01:09,410
Jin Hee! Let's play!

13
00:01:15,670 --> 00:01:19,120
Oh, hello. Can I play with Jin Hee?

14
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:22,080
Wait just a bit. I'll be right there.

15
00:01:28,040 --> 00:01:30,460
Not him. He's too nice.

16
00:01:30,460 --> 00:01:32,560
What's wrong with nice?

17
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:35,970
Listen to me carefully.

18
00:01:35,970 --> 00:01:40,060
If a man is too nice and he does everything you ask for,

19
00:01:40,060 --> 00:01:44,480
he'd end up making you do everything.

20
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:46,480
Men like that...

21
00:01:47,530 --> 00:01:48,590
are fools.

22
00:01:48,590 --> 00:01:51,530
[Episode 7: A fool]

23
00:01:51,530 --> 00:01:53,880
Oppa, you must've waited a long time.

24
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:56,210
Not at all. Welcome.

25
00:01:59,580 --> 00:02:01,450
Hello.

26
00:02:04,190 --> 00:02:05,720
What?

27
00:02:09,970 --> 00:02:12,300
I'll see myself out now.

28
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:15,780
Where are you going?

29
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:25,590
Oppa, this is mine.

30
00:02:25,590 --> 00:02:27,150
Yes.

31
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:31,950
Let's go.

32
00:02:37,630 --> 00:02:39,400
Hey.

33
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:41,330
Hey.

34
00:02:54,080 --> 00:02:57,410
So you rented the car that early in the morning and drove?

35
00:02:57,410 --> 00:02:59,510
You probably didn't get any sleep.

36
00:02:59,510 --> 00:03:01,020
Aren't you tired?

37
00:03:01,020 --> 00:03:04,740
I'm okay. This is nothing.

38
00:03:08,380 --> 00:03:10,460
- Would you like some?
- Pardon?

39
00:03:10,460 --> 00:03:12,420
It's a yellow light!

40
00:03:16,050 --> 00:03:17,760
It happens...

41
00:03:17,760 --> 00:03:19,730
He could make a mistake.

42
00:03:19,730 --> 00:03:21,600
It's a yellow light.

43
00:03:23,930 --> 00:03:25,760
Hey! It was a yellow light!

44
00:03:25,760 --> 00:03:27,830
It was a yellow light!

45
00:03:27,830 --> 00:03:29,780
Get it together.

46
00:03:29,780 --> 00:03:30,580
Hey!

47
00:03:30,580 --> 00:03:33,920
Oppa! Why do you drive like this?

48
00:03:33,920 --> 00:03:36,970
- Gosh!
- Well...

49
00:03:38,140 --> 00:03:42,080
Ahjussi, candy fell.

50
00:03:56,630 --> 00:03:59,000
My gosh. You can see the ocean?

51
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:02,450
- Hold on.
- There are yachts, too. My gosh.

52
00:04:03,550 --> 00:04:05,980
It's a boat. Is it a boat?

53
00:04:05,980 --> 00:04:08,410
Wow! You can see the ocean from here, too.

54
00:04:08,410 --> 00:04:10,790
Ocean view.

55
00:04:11,740 --> 00:04:13,480
Mom.

56
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:15,370
Mom.

57
00:04:15,370 --> 00:04:17,380
- Mom.
- I choose that room!

58
00:04:17,380 --> 00:04:19,190
I'll choose that one, then—

59
00:04:19,190 --> 00:04:20,870
What? What is it?

60
00:04:20,870 --> 00:04:22,570
Hey!

61
00:04:25,890 --> 00:04:27,840
- What's the plan?
- What plan?

62
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:29,300
Why are you asking me that?

63
00:04:29,300 --> 00:04:31,220
The one who started it needs to tell me.

64
00:04:31,220 --> 00:04:33,880
No need to worry. Just think of him as a sugar daddy.

65
00:04:33,880 --> 00:04:37,880
He said he stayed up all night researching restaurants and tour spots.

66
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:39,530
To spend money.

67
00:04:39,530 --> 00:04:41,670
Isn't he commendable?

68
00:04:47,070 --> 00:04:49,810
That's enough. It's not even a big deal.

69
00:04:49,810 --> 00:04:53,510
You're making him wait outside. How could you be so rude?

70
00:04:56,270 --> 00:04:59,060
What's wrong with her, anyway?

71
00:05:04,010 --> 00:05:08,150
You should've just had a drink with her in Seoul if you wanted to make up with her.

72
00:05:08,150 --> 00:05:10,850
Why did you have to come all the way here and cause trouble?

73
00:05:10,850 --> 00:05:12,230
Just look at us.

74
00:05:12,230 --> 00:05:14,030
Shut up.

75
00:05:15,670 --> 00:05:19,640
I mean, I have to work.

76
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:23,770
Who's the one who wanted to enjoy things two days in advance?

77
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:28,910
I have to just let her win right now. Right?

78
00:05:28,910 --> 00:05:30,760
Isn't it obvious?

79
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:32,930
Seriously...

80
00:05:43,180 --> 00:05:47,050
- Hey, take one with a yacht. Yacht, yacht, yacht.
- What?

81
00:05:47,050 --> 00:05:50,900
Gosh. Yacht, my foot. Just take one alone.

82
00:05:50,900 --> 00:05:54,440
- From here, I'll—
- I'm hungry.

83
00:05:54,440 --> 00:05:56,420
What should we eat?

84
00:05:57,290 --> 00:05:58,520
There's a place I found.

85
00:05:58,520 --> 00:06:00,120
I want red-banded lobsters.

86
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:02,790
- Red-banded lobsters?
- I want meat.

87
00:06:02,790 --> 00:06:04,570
There's a famous galbi place here.

88
00:06:04,570 --> 00:06:06,660
Jin Soo, what would you like?

89
00:06:06,660 --> 00:06:08,180
I can eat anything.

90
00:06:08,180 --> 00:06:09,990
Let's have galbi today, then.

91
00:06:09,990 --> 00:06:11,420
Okay.

92
00:06:12,700 --> 00:06:15,410
What? We're having red-banded lobsters.

93
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:20,340
Oppa, what would you like?

94
00:06:20,340 --> 00:06:23,460
Galbi or red-banded lobsters?

95
00:06:35,290 --> 00:06:37,410
Let's have red-banded lobsters. Looks like she found a place.

96
00:06:37,410 --> 00:06:39,440
I don't want to peel all those.

97
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:40,810
I said I was hungry.

98
00:06:40,810 --> 00:06:43,260
I'll peel them for you.

99
00:07:07,630 --> 00:07:09,360
Aren't you going to eat?

100
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:11,240
You go ahead.

101
00:07:14,860 --> 00:07:16,020
Oh, yeah.

102
00:07:16,020 --> 00:07:18,250
How come you're not eating, Oppa? Have some.

103
00:07:18,250 --> 00:07:20,910
I'm okay. Help yourself.

104
00:07:20,910 --> 00:07:22,660
Come on.

105
00:07:22,660 --> 00:07:24,280
Here.

106
00:07:27,610 --> 00:07:29,290
Well...

107
00:07:30,010 --> 00:07:32,810
Do you not like lobster, by chance?

108
00:07:32,810 --> 00:07:35,310
I-It's not that.

109
00:07:35,310 --> 00:07:40,410
Actually, I'm allergic to shellfish.

110
00:07:42,300 --> 00:07:44,330
Shellfish?

111
00:07:44,330 --> 00:07:48,410
So you can't eat shrimp, crab, lobster, and stuff like that?

112
00:07:52,070 --> 00:07:55,540
Why did you suggest coming here if you can't even eat it?

113
00:07:55,540 --> 00:07:58,200
I'm here to peel the lobsters for you.

114
00:07:58,200 --> 00:08:00,830
Seriously...

115
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,830
Over here.

116
00:08:09,020 --> 00:08:10,620
This has no shrimp or crab in it, right?

117
00:08:10,620 --> 00:08:12,070
I mentioned the allergy.

118
00:08:12,070 --> 00:08:14,930
Of course, there's none of that.

119
00:08:14,930 --> 00:08:17,110
Enjoy.

120
00:08:20,390 --> 00:08:23,330
Wow, it's so nice and spicy.

121
00:08:23,330 --> 00:08:25,390
Try some.

122
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:29,570
Okay...

123
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:36,940
Wow! This is it.

124
00:08:36,940 --> 00:08:39,500
- It's tasty.
- Isn't it?

125
00:08:44,080 --> 00:08:46,680
Hey. It'd be a waste to eat it like this.

126
00:08:46,680 --> 00:08:48,340
- Let's get soju.
- No.

127
00:08:48,340 --> 00:08:49,820
You want to get drunk even before unpacking?

128
00:08:49,820 --> 00:08:52,100
So what if we get drunk? We're on vacation.

129
00:08:52,100 --> 00:08:53,350
Get drunk later if you want to.

130
00:08:53,350 --> 00:08:54,900
I found a bar for us.

131
00:08:54,900 --> 00:08:57,330
You already planned it all out.

132
00:08:57,330 --> 00:09:01,020
I'll save it for tonight, then.

133
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:05,760
What's wrong, Oppa? Is it spicy?

134
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:08,940
Huh? No, no. It's not too bad.

135
00:09:08,940 --> 00:09:11,610
Looks like it's too spicy for you.

136
00:09:11,610 --> 00:09:15,990
Try putting the broth in the rice. It'd be a lot better.

137
00:09:26,300 --> 00:09:28,170
Mom.

138
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:33,830
Are they out of their mind?

139
00:09:33,830 --> 00:09:37,530
They should've checked properly if we had mentioned the allergy.

140
00:09:37,530 --> 00:09:41,360
The chef was basically a kid. I should've twisted his neck.

141
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:43,660
Seriously...

142
00:09:43,660 --> 00:09:45,190
It's okay, Oppa.

143
00:09:45,190 --> 00:09:47,980
The doctor said it was a relief we came early.

144
00:09:47,980 --> 00:09:49,260
You'll be okay soon.

145
00:09:49,260 --> 00:09:51,560
Also, since I work at the hospital,

146
00:09:51,560 --> 00:09:56,170
stuff like this is considered nothing. I've seen it all.

147
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:08,010
You're better than I thought.

148
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:11,750
Am I really okay?

149
00:10:13,270 --> 00:10:14,770
It's so upsetting.

150
00:10:14,770 --> 00:10:17,810
I didn't want you to see me like this.

151
00:10:19,110 --> 00:10:20,310
Why didn't you tell me?

152
00:10:20,310 --> 00:10:24,250
Why did you say to go there to peel the lobsters you can't even eat?

153
00:10:24,250 --> 00:10:27,580
I know. Why did I do that?

154
00:10:27,580 --> 00:10:31,060
I should've prepared for the worst.

155
00:10:31,060 --> 00:10:33,100
Get up.

156
00:10:33,100 --> 00:10:34,620
Let's leave now.

157
00:10:34,620 --> 00:10:36,940
I have a favor to ask, Eun Mi.

158
00:10:37,730 --> 00:10:42,450
I really don't want Jin Hee to see me like this.

159
00:10:42,450 --> 00:10:45,810
Could you get me a mask?

160
00:10:45,810 --> 00:10:48,080
A mask.

161
00:10:49,810 --> 00:10:51,940
Okay, wait just a moment.

162
00:10:51,940 --> 00:10:55,620
You can pay at the reception, Ma'am.

163
00:11:27,910 --> 00:11:29,880
Oppa.

164
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:31,760
I'll step out for a second.

165
00:11:31,760 --> 00:11:33,230
Are you sure you're okay?

166
00:11:33,230 --> 00:11:34,610
Yes.

167
00:11:34,610 --> 00:11:36,980
Go have fun.

168
00:11:36,980 --> 00:11:38,560
What?

169
00:11:39,260 --> 00:11:41,380
Go have fun.

170
00:11:42,060 --> 00:11:44,100
See you later.

171
00:11:45,860 --> 00:11:47,890
Can we just leave him?

172
00:11:47,890 --> 00:11:50,270
He can't drink even if he comes.

173
00:11:50,270 --> 00:11:51,840
Let's just drink by ourselves.

174
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:52,850
- Let's go.
- Okay!

175
00:11:52,850 --> 00:11:55,010
The three of us can do that thing.

176
00:11:55,010 --> 00:11:56,800
The thing we didn't get to do last time.

177
00:11:56,800 --> 00:11:58,670
You mean a girl group?

178
00:11:58,670 --> 00:12:00,530
This isn't good.

179
00:12:00,530 --> 00:12:02,120
You guys should go without me.

180
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:03,560
What?

181
00:12:03,560 --> 00:12:06,170
He sure is making me worry.

182
00:12:06,170 --> 00:12:08,220
Well, you can't do that...

183
00:12:08,220 --> 00:12:10,980
Mom. Mo—

184
00:12:21,210 --> 00:12:23,910
How could she be so selfish?

185
00:12:23,910 --> 00:12:27,020
I'm crazy for being happy just for a second.

186
00:12:27,020 --> 00:12:28,850
And him, too.

187
00:12:28,850 --> 00:12:30,370
Why did he create a situation like this?

188
00:12:30,370 --> 00:12:34,320
We wouldn't have gone there if he said he was allergic from the beginning.

189
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:36,290
And why did he have to join our trip?

190
00:12:36,290 --> 00:12:38,940
Doesn't he feel uncomfortable with me? Does he know me?

191
00:12:42,460 --> 00:12:44,800
Hey, say something.

192
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:47,400
Can you understand my mom and that man?

193
00:12:48,870 --> 00:12:50,460
You know...

194
00:12:50,460 --> 00:12:53,390
Since you ruined my much-awaited rest and

195
00:12:53,390 --> 00:12:55,620
things aren't working out for you,

196
00:12:55,620 --> 00:12:57,770
it makes me so happy.

197
00:12:58,600 --> 00:13:01,320
I guess life is fair.

198
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:02,830
What goes around comes around.

199
00:13:02,830 --> 00:13:04,800
Justice prevails.

200
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:06,460
Come empty, return empty.

201
00:13:06,460 --> 00:13:10,450
Shut up, or I'll send you the bill for 1.8 million won.

202
00:13:11,370 --> 00:13:16,640
I think Ahjumma already forgot she had a fight with you.

203
00:13:16,640 --> 00:13:18,760
Her head is completely occupied with him.

204
00:13:18,760 --> 00:13:21,750
Hey, how could she possibly forget that?

205
00:13:21,750 --> 00:13:25,050
I'm saying it felt like it was my fault!

206
00:13:25,800 --> 00:13:30,400
I don't want to be treated like goldfish poop by him, too!

207
00:13:32,760 --> 00:13:35,230
I hurt her feelings so much.

208
00:13:35,230 --> 00:13:37,580
You know how she is.

209
00:13:38,570 --> 00:13:40,280
Give me a break.

210
00:13:41,380 --> 00:13:45,040
There's no way she could forget that.

211
00:13:48,520 --> 00:13:50,100
It's so funny.

212
00:13:50,100 --> 00:13:51,260
Don't laugh?

213
00:13:51,260 --> 00:13:54,700
Oppa, Oppa... d-did you hear that?

214
00:14:01,070 --> 00:14:04,050
Are you sleepy? Tired?

215
00:14:04,050 --> 00:14:05,630
No.

216
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:15,160
It's past 10:30.

217
00:14:15,160 --> 00:14:16,650
They're coming back late.

218
00:14:16,650 --> 00:14:18,800
It's an unfamiliar area, too.

219
00:14:19,430 --> 00:14:21,940
She's with Jin Soo. Don't worry.

220
00:14:24,370 --> 00:14:26,810
What's Jin Soo like?

221
00:14:26,810 --> 00:14:29,680
He seems to have a good personality.

222
00:14:29,680 --> 00:14:32,620
He's basically family.

223
00:14:32,620 --> 00:14:33,890
Family?

224
00:14:33,890 --> 00:14:36,470
I've known him since Jin Hee was in kindergarten.

225
00:14:36,470 --> 00:14:40,160
He stays with us instead of staying with his parents whenever he's in Seoul.

226
00:14:40,160 --> 00:14:42,280
He's more comfortable with us.

227
00:14:43,020 --> 00:14:44,910
It's always been like that.

228
00:14:48,010 --> 00:14:51,440
By the way, you're concerned about Jin Hee a lot.

229
00:14:52,320 --> 00:14:54,810
Of course.

230
00:14:54,810 --> 00:14:56,890
She's your daughter.

231
00:14:58,400 --> 00:14:59,930
I see.

232
00:15:00,860 --> 00:15:04,560
By the way, why did you follow us here?

233
00:15:21,580 --> 00:15:25,060
Look at you... Look at you.

234
00:15:25,060 --> 00:15:27,810
How can you sleep when I'm next to you?

235
00:16:33,300 --> 00:16:36,510
So it didn't become an open investigation. Right?

236
00:16:36,510 --> 00:16:39,860
The victim's ex-boyfriend remains the suspect, too.

237
00:16:39,860 --> 00:16:42,370
Got it. Thank you, Senior.

238
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:48,880
Of course, I'm doing well.

239
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:51,900
I need to get going. I'll talk to you again.

240
00:17:13,230 --> 00:17:15,320
Senior.

241
00:17:17,620 --> 00:17:19,430
Hello?

242
00:17:19,430 --> 00:17:21,090
What?

243
00:17:21,760 --> 00:17:23,430
Why won't he say anything?

244
00:17:25,330 --> 00:17:27,780
- Hello?
- Are you drunk?

245
00:17:27,780 --> 00:17:29,230
What?

246
00:17:30,900 --> 00:17:32,900
Senior!

247
00:17:32,900 --> 00:17:35,020
Hello!

248
00:17:36,130 --> 00:17:37,540
Your junior was upset.

249
00:17:37,540 --> 00:17:39,710
So I drank a bit.

250
00:17:39,710 --> 00:17:41,450
Let's talk later. Hang up.

251
00:17:41,450 --> 00:17:42,990
Huh?

252
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:45,030
You're drunk.

253
00:17:45,030 --> 00:17:47,180
Let's talk when you're sober. Bye.

254
00:17:47,180 --> 00:17:48,810
Wow!

255
00:17:48,810 --> 00:17:53,120
When you were drunk out of your mind,

256
00:17:53,120 --> 00:17:55,700
I suffered so much because of you.

257
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:58,620
But you're ignoring me like this?

258
00:17:58,620 --> 00:18:00,130
That's enough—

259
00:18:00,130 --> 00:18:01,990
You know...

260
00:18:01,990 --> 00:18:06,070
I... dragged your huge body

261
00:18:06,070 --> 00:18:11,340
and I looked for the key among a bunch of other keys with my tiny hands...

262
00:18:11,340 --> 00:18:14,120
I should've just left you on the street...

263
00:18:14,120 --> 00:18:15,770
Hey.

264
00:18:24,630 --> 00:18:27,610
I'm letting it slide because you're Eun Jae Won.

265
00:18:28,530 --> 00:18:31,370
You need to know that, Senior.

266
00:18:31,370 --> 00:18:34,020
Why did you do that to me, by the way?

267
00:18:35,300 --> 00:18:36,710
I'm sorry.

268
00:18:36,710 --> 00:18:39,180
I'll tell her to call you when she's sober.

269
00:18:39,180 --> 00:18:41,250
- Hello?
- Well, hello.

270
00:18:41,250 --> 00:18:42,710
I've seen you twice.

271
00:18:42,710 --> 00:18:44,650
I'm Kim Jin Soo.

272
00:18:45,350 --> 00:18:47,120
Oh, yes, I remember. Hello.

273
00:18:47,120 --> 00:18:48,770
Why did you do that to me then?

274
00:18:48,770 --> 00:18:51,420
