292
00:20:00,930 --> 00:20:03,680
Hey, that's enough. Forget about everything.

293
00:20:03,680 --> 00:20:06,630
Let's split up if we're going to be this way. Jin Soo!

294
00:20:06,630 --> 00:20:10,850
Oh, he left early in the morning.

295
00:20:15,390 --> 00:20:18,390
Whatever! We're still splitting up.

296
00:20:19,040 --> 00:20:20,070
Are you serious right now?

297
00:20:20,070 --> 00:20:23,110
I'm not sure about that, either.

298
00:20:27,660 --> 00:20:29,370
What do you think, then, Oppa?

299
00:20:29,370 --> 00:20:33,340
- Huh?
- You're not sure about splitting up.

300
00:20:33,340 --> 00:20:35,070
Which side are you on?

301
00:20:35,070 --> 00:20:36,210
What?

302
00:20:36,210 --> 00:20:37,720
He's obviously on your side.

303
00:20:37,720 --> 00:20:40,290
Why would you even ask that?

304
00:20:40,290 --> 00:20:41,600
I looked into it, too.

305
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:45,410
Going to the lighthouse first is efficient.

306
00:20:45,410 --> 00:20:47,930
- What?
- And we can take the cable car

307
00:20:47,930 --> 00:20:50,990
and drive along the coast, too.

308
00:20:52,470 --> 00:20:54,640
Sir, what are you doing right now?

309
00:20:54,640 --> 00:20:56,260
Pardon?

310
00:20:56,260 --> 00:20:59,570
How could he be so bad at reading the air?

311
00:21:01,450 --> 00:21:02,980
Mom!

312
00:21:02,980 --> 00:21:04,820
Mom!

313
00:21:06,430 --> 00:21:08,370
Tell me.

314
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:10,300
I'm not going!

315
00:21:10,300 --> 00:21:12,100
I'm not!

316
00:21:29,970 --> 00:21:32,800
Pretend like you're holding the lighthouse.

317
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:34,500
Like you're holding it.

318
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:35,980
No, like this.

319
00:21:35,980 --> 00:21:38,090
Oh, on the palm?

320
00:21:38,090 --> 00:21:41,430
Look over here. I'll take a photo of you.

321
00:21:41,430 --> 00:21:43,910
Okay.

322
00:21:43,910 --> 00:21:45,930
Okay.

323
00:21:45,930 --> 00:21:51,260
One, two.

324
00:21:51,260 --> 00:21:54,160
Okay.

325
00:21:54,160 --> 00:21:55,600
One...

326
00:21:55,600 --> 00:21:58,750
♫ I was thinking of listening more ♫

327
00:21:58,750 --> 00:22:03,710
♫ But I can't stand it. I'm crazy, yeah. ♫

328
00:22:03,710 --> 00:22:06,650
♫ Stand by, my eyes are focused ♫

329
00:22:06,650 --> 00:22:09,750
I'll take one from here.

330
00:22:09,750 --> 00:22:11,110
One—

331
00:22:11,110 --> 00:22:14,400
♫ Hey, look at me ♫

332
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:19,460
♫ Let's get it on and on, baby. Let's get it on ♫

333
00:22:19,460 --> 00:22:26,170
♫ Your voice is driving me crazy. Please tell me ♫

334
00:22:26,170 --> 00:22:29,830
Oppa, you should take photos from down there.

335
00:22:29,830 --> 00:22:31,020
Okay.

336
00:22:31,020 --> 00:22:37,160
♫ I said you love me now, baby. What a wonderful night ♫

337
00:22:37,160 --> 00:22:42,620
Look over here! One, two...

338
00:22:43,530 --> 00:22:44,860
Send this to me.

339
00:22:44,860 --> 00:22:45,850
How about this one?

340
00:22:45,850 --> 00:22:49,470
♫ K-K-Kiss me. L-L-Love ♫

341
00:22:49,470 --> 00:22:51,610
This is my favorite.

342
00:23:02,120 --> 00:23:05,080
Won't you take photos with him, by the way?

343
00:23:05,850 --> 00:23:08,030
Will you take them for us?

344
00:23:08,030 --> 00:23:10,220
Take selfies.

345
00:23:11,160 --> 00:23:13,990
I don't like him as much as I thought.

346
00:23:13,990 --> 00:23:18,930
We have nothing in common, including diet and lifestyle.

347
00:23:19,630 --> 00:23:20,780
Are you saying that now?

348
00:23:20,780 --> 00:23:24,070
Hey, he goes to bed at 10:00.

349
00:23:24,070 --> 00:23:25,870
And he wakes up at 4:00 in the morning.

350
00:23:25,870 --> 00:23:28,340
I asked him what he does so early.

351
00:23:29,040 --> 00:23:31,170
He apparently reads.

352
00:23:31,170 --> 00:23:33,060
He works out and drinks tea.

353
00:23:33,060 --> 00:23:35,990
Isn't he like the least fun person?

354
00:23:35,990 --> 00:23:38,410
And why is he so servile?

355
00:23:38,410 --> 00:23:41,520
He was a dork when he was a kid,

356
00:23:41,520 --> 00:23:43,220
but I liked how feisty he was.

357
00:23:43,220 --> 00:23:46,530
Why did you even bring him if you hadn't checked him out first?

358
00:23:46,530 --> 00:23:48,610
I know.

359
00:23:48,610 --> 00:23:51,500
Why did I bring him here, anyway?

360
00:23:53,210 --> 00:23:54,950
Hey...

361
00:23:54,950 --> 00:23:57,100
This is no fun.

362
00:23:57,100 --> 00:23:59,100
Let's go on the cable car.

363
00:23:59,100 --> 00:24:00,680
No, no, no.

364
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:04,230
There's a hidden beach if you go a little further.

365
00:24:04,230 --> 00:24:05,910
If you go up there,

366
00:24:05,910 --> 00:24:10,660
you'll see a view that'd make you forgive him for everything.

367
00:24:10,660 --> 00:24:12,950
Your heart will feel like... Wow!

368
00:24:12,950 --> 00:24:16,510
Wow! What a view!

369
00:24:16,510 --> 00:24:18,760
It's not the same as this!

370
00:24:18,760 --> 00:24:20,770
- Here.
- Mom.

371
00:24:22,710 --> 00:24:24,800
I'll take nice photos of you there.

372
00:24:24,800 --> 00:24:26,930
We just need to go a little further.

373
00:24:26,930 --> 00:24:29,760
Done. Let's say we saw it.

374
00:24:32,510 --> 00:24:34,320
Why do you keep leaning?

375
00:24:34,320 --> 00:24:35,370
Did you drink already?

376
00:24:35,370 --> 00:24:37,270
The bathroom must be on the first floor. Right?

377
00:24:37,270 --> 00:24:39,720
I need to get in line. Do you want to go without me?

378
00:24:39,720 --> 00:24:42,130
We need to go together.

379
00:24:42,130 --> 00:24:43,900
Oppa.

380
00:24:44,950 --> 00:24:46,920
Oppa! What are you doing?

381
00:24:46,920 --> 00:24:48,480
No, it's nothing.

382
00:24:48,480 --> 00:24:51,060
What is it? Do you need something?

383
00:24:51,060 --> 00:24:52,880
Never mind.

384
00:25:07,700 --> 00:25:09,170
Do you want some coffee or something?

385
00:25:09,170 --> 00:25:11,940
I'll go get it. What would you like?

386
00:25:11,940 --> 00:25:13,340
Looks like the line is moving fast.

387
00:25:13,340 --> 00:25:15,570
You can drink it in the cable car.

388
00:25:15,570 --> 00:25:17,720
- No. You can't drink in there.
- Honey, wake up!

389
00:25:17,720 --> 00:25:20,460
- Is that so?
- Somebody, please help!

390
00:25:20,460 --> 00:25:22,650
- Hold on.
- What's wrong!

391
00:25:22,650 --> 00:25:24,010
What do we do?

392
00:25:24,010 --> 00:25:25,880
What's going on?

393
00:25:25,880 --> 00:25:26,990
Mom.

394
00:25:29,530 --> 00:25:32,750
Honey, Honey, what's wrong? Wake up!

395
00:25:32,750 --> 00:25:34,530
Please help!

396
00:25:34,530 --> 00:25:35,740
Wake up!

397
00:25:35,740 --> 00:25:37,900
Step aside! Step aside.

398
00:25:37,900 --> 00:25:39,680
Step aside.

399
00:25:43,700 --> 00:25:45,400
What is it, Oppa?

400
00:25:45,400 --> 00:25:46,380
I think it's CVA.
[CVA: Cerebral Vascular Accident]

401
00:25:46,380 --> 00:25:48,460
CVA? A stroke?

402
00:25:48,460 --> 00:25:49,410
Somebody, please call 911.

403
00:25:49,410 --> 00:25:51,030
I can do it.

404
00:25:51,030 --> 00:25:53,710
I'm at the cable car station at Yeosu Marine Park. There's an emergency patient.

405
00:25:53,710 --> 00:25:56,330
- It's a stroke.
- He's showing symptoms of a stroke.

406
00:25:56,330 --> 00:25:58,670
A doctor is giving him emergency treatment at the scene. Please hurry.

407
00:25:58,670 --> 00:26:01,560
Looks like the tongue is okay. How's the pulse?

408
00:26:01,560 --> 00:26:02,850
It's too slow.

409
00:26:02,850 --> 00:26:05,250
- Honey!
- You can't give him water.

410
00:26:05,250 --> 00:26:07,970
Does he take blood pressure medicine by chance?

411
00:26:07,970 --> 00:26:09,560
Yes, he has high blood pressure.

412
00:26:09,560 --> 00:26:11,840
I noticed he was strange earlier, too.

413
00:26:11,840 --> 00:26:13,860
Sir, can you hear me?

414
00:26:13,860 --> 00:26:15,320
Try blinking if you can!

415
00:26:15,320 --> 00:26:16,920
Honey!

416
00:26:16,920 --> 00:26:18,910
Good job! You have to stay awake.

417
00:26:18,910 --> 00:26:21,330
You can't fall asleep even if you get sleepy.

418
00:26:22,010 --> 00:26:23,710
No, you can't massage him.

419
00:26:23,710 --> 00:26:25,790
Just raise his body temperature with the blanket.

420
00:26:25,790 --> 00:26:27,120
Listen to me carefully, Ma'am.

421
00:26:27,120 --> 00:26:30,190
What you can do now is to keep talking to him

422
00:26:30,190 --> 00:26:32,150
so he doesn't black out. You can do that. Right?

423
00:26:32,150 --> 00:26:33,600
Yes, I can do it.

424
00:26:33,600 --> 00:26:36,530
Honey! Wake up, Honey.

425
00:26:36,530 --> 00:26:40,460
Open your eyes, please.

426
00:26:40,460 --> 00:26:42,310
It's improving.

427
00:26:42,310 --> 00:26:43,950
You're doing great, sir.

428
00:26:43,950 --> 00:26:45,910
Hang in there just a little longer.

429
00:26:45,910 --> 00:26:48,440
Honey! Open your eyes!

430
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:50,320
Nice!

431
00:27:02,540 --> 00:27:04,800
I'm so tired.

432
00:27:06,090 --> 00:27:07,800
Thank you so much.

433
00:27:07,800 --> 00:27:08,830
Thank you.

434
00:27:08,830 --> 00:27:13,290
It's such a relief that we had you at the scene.

435
00:27:13,290 --> 00:27:15,810
I'll exchange your tickets. Take the ride now.

436
00:27:15,810 --> 00:27:18,320
If you take it now, you'll see the sunset.

437
00:27:18,320 --> 00:27:20,260
Really?

438
00:27:20,260 --> 00:27:22,520
Thank you so much.

439
00:27:22,520 --> 00:27:24,380
- Thank you.
- Thank you so much!

440
00:27:24,380 --> 00:27:25,480
Thank you!

441
00:27:25,480 --> 00:27:27,230
Mom, let's take it right now.

442
00:27:27,230 --> 00:27:29,800
I don't want to. I'm tired. I can't.

443
00:27:29,800 --> 00:27:31,250
My heart is racing.

444
00:27:31,250 --> 00:27:33,730
We came this far. Do you just want to leave?

445
00:27:33,730 --> 00:27:35,580
I'll give you a piggyback ride if you're tired.

446
00:27:35,580 --> 00:27:36,690
Yes, let's take it.

447
00:27:36,690 --> 00:27:39,440
We came this far. Let's go.

448
00:27:39,440 --> 00:27:41,050
I'm sorry.

449
00:27:44,080 --> 00:27:45,610
Hey!

450
00:27:45,610 --> 00:27:48,660
Didn't you see us working our butt off to save someone just now?

451
00:27:48,660 --> 00:27:52,240
How could you suggest taking the ride instead of taking a break?

452
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:55,440
Because she said we'd catch the sunset if we take it now.

453
00:27:55,440 --> 00:27:57,630
And you'd feel better if you saw a nice view—

454
00:27:57,630 --> 00:28:00,320
Yes, it's because this is our only chance.

455
00:28:00,320 --> 00:28:03,440
I'm okay. We can just—

456
00:28:03,440 --> 00:28:06,010
Were you born to be a fool?

457
00:28:06,010 --> 00:28:08,920
Or don't you know how to read the air?

458
00:28:10,810 --> 00:28:12,920
Well, Eun Mi.

459
00:28:12,920 --> 00:28:15,130
Eun Mi!

460
00:28:15,130 --> 00:28:17,100
Eun Mi!

461
00:28:20,230 --> 00:28:22,810
What's wrong with her?

462
00:28:45,310 --> 00:28:47,740
I guess I'm sorry.

463
00:28:51,620 --> 00:28:54,410
I'm really sorry!

464
00:29:00,660 --> 00:29:03,690
I'm so freaking sorry. Okay?

465
00:29:53,870 --> 00:29:58,590
Could you tell me if I did anything wrong?

466
00:29:58,590 --> 00:30:00,940
So I can fix it.

467
00:30:01,640 --> 00:30:05,300
Is it because I've been making you tired since yesterday?

468
00:30:05,300 --> 00:30:06,770
Oppa.

469
00:30:06,770 --> 00:30:09,490
- Tell me.
- Why did you come here?

470
00:30:09,490 --> 00:30:13,790
You must've known it'd be difficult and uncomfortable.

471
00:30:13,790 --> 00:30:16,400
But why did you tag along?

472
00:30:23,850 --> 00:30:28,170
How about you? Why did you bring me here?

473
00:30:30,670 --> 00:30:33,940
Me? To seduce you.

474
00:30:33,940 --> 00:30:36,800
But why do you keep caring about Jin Hee?

475
00:30:36,800 --> 00:30:40,140
My daughter has nothing to do with you.

476
00:30:40,140 --> 00:30:43,600
Why are you trying to become close to her?

477
00:30:46,050 --> 00:30:50,200
If you can't take a hint even after warning you multiple times,

478
00:30:50,200 --> 00:30:53,580
you can't date me. Don't you think?

479
00:31:12,480 --> 00:31:14,550
I'm sorry.

480
00:31:15,500 --> 00:31:19,300
I didn't think through things.

481
00:31:19,300 --> 00:31:21,940
No, I put you two in a difficult position.

482
00:31:21,940 --> 00:31:23,840
I'm sorry.

483
00:31:23,840 --> 00:31:26,430
Eun Mi, I'm sorry.

484
00:31:26,430 --> 00:31:28,540
You're right.

485
00:31:28,540 --> 00:31:30,730
I apologize.

486
00:31:31,370 --> 00:31:35,400
It won't ever happen again.

487
00:32:07,100 --> 00:32:10,980
Do you want to stop by a souvenir store tomorrow?

488
00:32:10,980 --> 00:32:13,010
There's a place Jin Soo recommended.

489
00:32:13,010 --> 00:32:15,020
Sure, whatever.

490
00:32:17,620 --> 00:32:19,160
Did you two fight?

491
00:32:19,160 --> 00:32:21,570
What are we, kids? Why would we fight?

492
00:32:21,570 --> 00:32:24,670
If you're worried about me, you don't have to be.

493
00:32:24,670 --> 00:32:27,380
Did I ever worry about you while dating?

494
00:32:27,380 --> 00:32:31,600
That's why I said, "If." Didn't I?

495
00:32:33,160 --> 00:32:37,570
I don't know about the rest, but I won't let you be called a goldfish poop again.

496
00:32:37,570 --> 00:32:42,070
I'm sorry I let you hear about

497
00:32:42,070 --> 00:32:44,370
the goldfish poop.

498
00:32:45,280 --> 00:32:47,170
I apologize.

499
00:32:50,820 --> 00:32:52,570
It's okay.

500
00:32:54,060 --> 00:32:56,300
I was fine because...

501
00:32:56,300 --> 00:33:00,350
you pulled out all those women's hair, then.

502
00:33:01,990 --> 00:33:03,600
Is that so?

503
00:33:05,330 --> 00:33:07,300
It's your turn to apologize now.

504
00:33:07,300 --> 00:33:08,470
What?

505
00:33:08,470 --> 00:33:09,910
Apologize.

506
00:33:09,910 --> 00:33:12,620
That's why you came here.

507
00:33:12,620 --> 00:33:15,660
Go ahead and apologize.

508
00:33:24,080 --> 00:33:26,000
I'm sorry.

509
00:33:26,700 --> 00:33:29,200
I won't ever do that again.

510
00:33:29,200 --> 00:33:31,490
Okay, I accept.

511
00:33:36,610 --> 00:33:38,530
And one more thing.

512
00:33:38,530 --> 00:33:40,680
Don't jump the gun.

513
00:33:40,680 --> 00:33:43,700
He has nothing to do with you.

514
00:33:43,700 --> 00:33:46,360
If it turns out he's okay,

515
00:33:46,360 --> 00:33:48,090
he'll just be my boyfriend.

516
00:33:48,090 --> 00:33:53,370
So don't jump the gun and hate him or feel uncomfortable.

517
00:33:57,260 --> 00:33:59,150
Okay.

518
00:33:59,150 --> 00:34:00,870
Okay.

519
00:34:02,200 --> 00:34:03,960
Let's go.

520
00:34:53,930 --> 00:34:56,310
This is the CCTV footage from the bus stop you requested.

521
00:34:56,310 --> 00:34:58,320
I hope this helps.

522
00:35:17,340 --> 00:35:19,810
Is he dumb?

523
00:35:19,810 --> 00:35:23,030
Why is he letting her beat him if he didn't do anything wrong?

524
00:35:43,780 --> 00:35:46,030
What did you want to talk about?

525
00:35:48,530 --> 00:35:50,420
Give me your hands.

526
00:36:00,450 --> 00:36:02,890
Starting now, I'll...

527
00:36:03,700 --> 00:36:05,990
seduce you, too.

528
00:36:30,290 --> 00:36:33,260
Good luck with that, you fool.

529
00:36:34,740 --> 00:36:36,830
What a dumbass.

530
00:37:00,900 --> 00:37:03,270
You came out early.

531
00:37:03,270 --> 00:37:04,890
Why so early...

532
00:37:04,890 --> 00:37:07,660
Oh, you're here to see the sunrise.

533
00:37:07,660 --> 00:37:08,750
Yes.

534
00:37:08,750 --> 00:37:11,000
See you back inside, then.

535
00:37:12,880 --> 00:37:14,660
Excuse me.

536
00:37:18,610 --> 00:37:22,500
I was thinking about why I feel so uncomfortable and conflicted.

537
00:37:23,200 --> 00:37:26,370
I think we started off on the wrong foot.

538
00:37:26,370 --> 00:37:28,520
Both you and I.

539
00:37:30,180 --> 00:37:36,600
I was focusing too much on the fact that you were Mom's first love.

540
00:37:36,600 --> 00:37:39,560
The past is just the past.

541
00:37:40,210 --> 00:37:44,410
So I'll focus on the present from now on to keep things simple.

542
00:37:44,410 --> 00:37:48,150
What would you like me to do?

543
00:37:48,150 --> 00:37:49,850
Just...

544
00:37:50,920 --> 00:37:54,550
focus on being Mom's new love interest.

545
00:37:54,550 --> 00:37:57,770
Even if you succeed and become her boyfriend,

546
00:37:57,770 --> 00:38:00,160
only focus on her

547
00:38:00,160 --> 00:38:02,700
instead of worrying about me.

548
00:38:02,700 --> 00:38:06,820
Would you no longer feel uncomfortable, then?

549
00:38:08,270 --> 00:38:12,000
Yes. As long as you can do that,

550
00:38:12,700 --> 00:38:17,020
I'd feel comfortable seeing you anytime, Ahjussi.

551
00:38:21,240 --> 00:38:23,840
Okay, I'll do that.

552
00:38:23,840 --> 00:38:26,930
I'll only focus on her from now on.

553
00:38:26,930 --> 00:38:29,750
Do you have anything else to ask or tell me?

554
00:38:29,750 --> 00:38:32,560
Get it off your chest. I'm all ears.

555
00:38:34,500 --> 00:38:40,950
I'm grateful that you help her commute every morning and every night.

556
00:38:40,950 --> 00:38:43,690
It's not easy to do that every day.

557
00:38:43,690 --> 00:38:45,920
It's not like that at all.

558
00:38:45,920 --> 00:38:48,270
I'm really happy to do that.

559
00:38:48,270 --> 00:38:55,140
I just want you to trust me and rest easy.

560
00:38:55,140 --> 00:38:58,510
I'll do everything I can

561
00:38:58,510 --> 00:39:03,250
and if necessary, I'll make sure to protect her

562
00:39:03,250 --> 00:39:06,150
even if I have to risk my life.

563
00:39:07,080 --> 00:39:09,180
That's what I want to do.

564
00:39:22,010 --> 00:39:23,580
Are you leaving?

565
00:39:23,580 --> 00:39:26,190
I'm joining that team in the morning.

566
00:39:26,190 --> 00:39:29,100
- You're leaving today, too. Right?
- Yeah.

567
00:39:30,100 --> 00:39:31,790
Hey.

568
00:39:32,540 --> 00:39:34,910
I had fun, thanks to you.

569
00:39:34,910 --> 00:39:37,320
At least you know.

570
00:39:37,320 --> 00:39:39,480
You're okay. Right?

571
00:39:40,450 --> 00:39:42,690
He seems like an okay person.

572
00:39:43,510 --> 00:39:45,610
You're an okay person, too.

573
00:39:45,610 --> 00:39:47,540
I'm off.

574
00:39:57,660 --> 00:39:58,730
Should I play music?

575
00:39:58,730 --> 00:40:01,330
No, let's drive quietly.

576
00:40:01,330 --> 00:40:02,950
Okay.

577
00:40:04,870 --> 00:40:06,260
I'm hungry.

578
00:40:06,260 --> 00:40:08,500
What are we having for brunch?

579
00:40:08,500 --> 00:40:10,030
There's a place I found.

580
00:40:10,030 --> 00:40:12,560
We never got to eat octopus. Right?

581
00:40:12,560 --> 00:40:13,960
Octopus?

582
00:40:14,770 --> 00:40:17,150
What's the place you found?

583
00:40:17,150 --> 00:40:20,730
Well, there's a famous galbi place.

584
00:40:20,730 --> 00:40:23,110
Mom said she wanted that.

585
00:40:23,110 --> 00:40:25,170
How does galbi sound, Mom?

586
00:40:25,170 --> 00:40:27,150
We're having brunch. Galbi's no good.

587
00:40:27,150 --> 00:40:28,320
Let's have soup.

588
00:40:28,320 --> 00:40:31,630
They have soup, too. The beef is really tender, too.

589
00:40:31,630 --> 00:40:34,600
It was my friend's recommendation.

590
00:40:34,600 --> 00:40:36,570
Just count on me.

591
00:40:46,240 --> 00:40:49,230
♫ I wanted somebody special ♫

592
00:40:49,230 --> 00:40:51,060
Dip this in this sauce.

593
00:40:51,060 --> 00:40:53,180
It'd be even tastier.

594
00:40:53,180 --> 00:40:56,080
♫ That's right. Maybe you want me, too ♫

595
00:40:56,080 --> 00:40:58,470
♫ Do you also feel the same way? ♫

596
00:40:58,470 --> 00:41:02,120
It's so tender and tasty!

597
00:41:02,120 --> 00:41:05,500
♫ Everything's about you, you're my only best friend ♫

598
00:41:05,500 --> 00:41:07,350
I would've been sad if we missed out.

599
00:41:07,350 --> 00:41:08,570
It's so tasty.

600
00:41:08,570 --> 00:41:11,060
It's okay, Oppa. I can eat myself.

601
00:41:11,060 --> 00:41:12,480
Okay.

602
00:41:12,480 --> 00:41:15,250
Oh, there's a place with a nice view nearby.

603
00:41:15,250 --> 00:41:18,450
Should we stop by there, too?

604
00:41:18,450 --> 00:41:22,360
Did your friend recommend that place, too?

605
00:41:22,360 --> 00:41:25,710
♫ I have you at the end of a hard day ♫

606
00:41:25,710 --> 00:41:27,330
♫ Somebody like you ♫

607
00:41:27,330 --> 00:41:29,390
♫ Since you're always there ♫

608
00:41:29,390 --> 00:41:33,260
Wow! This place is so pretty.

609
00:41:33,260 --> 00:41:36,620
- So pretty.
- We're treating ourselves on the last day.

610
00:41:36,620 --> 00:41:38,570
- I know.
- Look at that!

611
00:41:38,570 --> 00:41:40,030
Let's take a picture.

612
00:41:40,030 --> 00:41:41,540
Okay.

613
00:41:41,540 --> 00:41:43,480
You have to take pictures at a place like this.

614
00:41:43,480 --> 00:41:45,510
Ahjussi, please take a picture of us.

615
00:41:45,510 --> 00:41:47,400
Okay.

616
00:41:49,310 --> 00:41:51,730
What?

617
00:41:51,730 --> 00:41:53,670
- It's nothing.
- Okay.

618
00:41:53,670 --> 00:41:56,200
One, two. So pretty.

619
00:41:56,200 --> 00:41:59,810
One more time. One, two.

620
00:41:59,810 --> 00:42:02,430
Another one.

621
00:42:02,430 --> 00:42:05,330
Okay. One, two.

622
00:42:05,330 --> 00:42:07,620
♫ Since you're always there ♫

623
00:42:07,620 --> 00:42:11,670
- Thank you.
- Have a look.

624
00:42:11,670 --> 00:42:14,880
So pretty.

625
00:42:14,880 --> 00:42:16,850
Oh, hold on.

626
00:42:16,850 --> 00:42:19,270
Take one with me, too.

627
00:42:19,270 --> 00:42:21,690
Yes, stand there. I'll take one for you.

628
00:42:21,690 --> 00:42:24,360
No, no! Let's take one together. There's a selfie mode.

629
00:42:24,360 --> 00:42:26,710
No, I want to take one with just you.

630
00:42:26,710 --> 00:42:28,990
We don't have a picture of just the two of us.

631
00:42:28,990 --> 00:42:30,880
I was actually pretty sad about it.

632
00:42:30,880 --> 00:42:32,870
So let's take one.

633
00:42:32,900 --> 00:42:34,400
Okay.

634
00:42:35,680 --> 00:42:39,610
I'll take it now. One, two, three.

635
00:42:39,610 --> 00:42:40,850
- Another one.
- Okay.

636
00:42:43,980 --> 00:42:46,870
One, two, three.

637
00:42:46,870 --> 00:42:49,960
- Nice. nice.
- Should we make a heart symbol?

638
00:42:49,960 --> 00:42:51,860
Really?

639
00:42:51,860 --> 00:42:54,060
One, two, three.

640
00:42:54,060 --> 00:42:56,530
- You asked me why I tagged along. Right?
- Yeah.

641
00:42:56,530 --> 00:43:00,080
I'll come wherever you are if you call me, Eun Mi.

642
00:43:00,080 --> 00:43:01,410
I don't need a reason.

643
00:43:01,410 --> 00:43:03,550
- Oppa.
- Yes.

644
00:43:06,160 --> 00:43:09,430
Be my boyfriend starting today.

645
00:43:09,430 --> 00:43:12,380
Why are you saying that here and now?

646
00:43:12,380 --> 00:43:14,200
Say hello.

647
00:43:14,200 --> 00:43:16,250
He's my boyfriend now.

648
00:43:16,250 --> 00:43:19,230
Park Jin Hong.

649
00:43:31,390 --> 00:43:36,840
Mom, didn't you say the men who do everything for you are fools? When I was a child?

650
00:43:36,840 --> 00:43:39,230
Yes, I remember.

651
00:43:39,230 --> 00:43:42,580
Your response was even more ridiculous.

652
00:43:42,580 --> 00:43:44,860
What did I say?

653
00:43:44,860 --> 00:43:45,940
"Mom..."

654
00:43:45,940 --> 00:43:51,100
Isn't an obedient fool better than a disobedient fool?

655
00:43:54,640 --> 00:43:56,200
I did?

656
00:43:56,200 --> 00:43:59,640
It was so funny that a little kid was saying that.

657
00:43:59,640 --> 00:44:02,760
I never paid attention to foolish men.

658
00:44:07,210 --> 00:44:09,030
I see.

659
00:44:10,000 --> 00:44:13,380
But isn't Ahjussi exactly that?

660
00:44:13,380 --> 00:44:15,820
An obedient fool.

661
00:44:17,820 --> 00:44:21,360
Yes, he's the fool to end all fools.

662
00:44:22,040 --> 00:44:24,080
You're right.

663
00:44:24,080 --> 00:44:27,700
Geez, I'm screwed.

664
00:44:27,700 --> 00:44:29,440
I'm screwed.

665
00:44:31,400 --> 00:44:33,600
[Tae Gyeong]

666
00:44:33,600 --> 00:44:35,330
A fool...

667
00:44:37,030 --> 00:44:38,930
Hey, Gyeong Tae.

668
00:44:41,960 --> 00:44:44,200
You went on a trip with Ahjumma's first love?

669
00:44:44,200 --> 00:44:47,110
- Yeah.
- First love...

670
00:44:48,700 --> 00:44:51,730
My gosh! Hey!

671
00:44:52,530 --> 00:44:54,860
Where did he come from out of the blue?

672
00:44:54,860 --> 00:44:57,900
I found out only recently, too.

673
00:44:57,900 --> 00:45:02,020
- Hey, the CCTV footage you sent me.
- Yeah.

674
00:45:02,020 --> 00:45:05,700
That was actually him. Mom's first love.

675
00:45:05,700 --> 00:45:08,910
Hey, why are you telling me this now?

676
00:45:08,910 --> 00:45:10,240
Because it's embarrassing.

677
00:45:10,240 --> 00:45:12,190
What is?

678
00:45:12,190 --> 00:45:17,610
It will put Mom in an awkward position if he's weird at all.

679
00:45:17,610 --> 00:45:21,050
Gosh, hey... Okay, I'll let it go. I will...

680
00:45:21,050 --> 00:45:23,830
Tell me right now. What's he like?

681
00:45:23,830 --> 00:45:26,670
Is his personality compatible with yours?

682
00:45:26,670 --> 00:45:30,060
Why do I matter? Mom's dating him. She's more important.

683
00:45:30,060 --> 00:45:32,630
Is that possible? He's your biological father.

684
00:45:32,630 --> 00:45:35,700
We won't even live together. Why does it matter?

685
00:45:35,700 --> 00:45:39,070
You share a bloodline. You're destined by Heaven.

686
00:45:40,750 --> 00:45:43,890
Gosh, that's too heavy.

687
00:45:43,890 --> 00:45:46,980
Hey, family is supposed to be heavy.

688
00:45:46,980 --> 00:45:49,450
You take responsibility, feel pressured,

689
00:45:49,450 --> 00:45:52,310
but it's so nice when you can depend on them.

690
00:45:52,310 --> 00:45:55,860
You can say that because you grew up in a huge family.

691
00:45:55,860 --> 00:45:57,450
I...

692
00:45:59,890 --> 00:46:03,490
I don't find him that different from her other boyfriends.

693
00:46:04,190 --> 00:46:09,090
Looks like you really live in a different world.

694
00:46:09,090 --> 00:46:11,040
It's so fascinating.

695
00:46:12,300 --> 00:46:13,970
Really?

696
00:46:15,810 --> 00:46:17,260
You shouldn't have bought all this.

697
00:46:17,260 --> 00:46:19,000
I picked that just for you, Captain Jang.

698
00:46:19,000 --> 00:46:22,600
- Really?
- Wow, my daughter will love this.

699
00:46:23,490 --> 00:46:27,030
Captain Cha, you look even better than I remember.

700
00:46:27,030 --> 00:46:31,390
His youngest daughter got into Dongsu University during rolling admissions.

701
00:46:31,390 --> 00:46:32,660
- Really?
- Yes.

702
00:46:32,660 --> 00:46:34,620
It's such a prestigious school.

703
00:46:35,310 --> 00:46:37,690
That's why you look so happy.

704
00:46:37,690 --> 00:46:39,830
Do you know how great of a daughter she is?

705
00:46:39,830 --> 00:46:44,580
She could've just resembled my face, but she resembled my brain, too.

706
00:46:49,040 --> 00:46:51,980
Chief, Team Leader brought us souvenirs.

707
00:46:51,980 --> 00:46:54,020
It's on your desk.

708
00:46:54,970 --> 00:46:56,800
- Team Leader Kim.
- Yes?

709
00:46:56,800 --> 00:46:59,700
- Talk to me after work.
- Why?

710
00:47:01,400 --> 00:47:03,580
Didn't that Kim Jin Soo fellow say anything?

711
00:47:03,580 --> 00:47:05,350
Jin Soo?

712
00:47:11,380 --> 00:47:14,340
[Calls: Eun Jae Won]

713
00:47:20,960 --> 00:47:23,960
[Eun Jae Won]
Why is this here?

714
00:47:23,960 --> 00:47:27,790
Why didn't that jerk Jin Soo say anything to me?

715
00:47:28,820 --> 00:47:30,460
Shit.

716
00:47:30,460 --> 00:47:34,800
Why isn't he picking up the phone?

717
00:47:34,800 --> 00:47:36,180
[Handmade Mugwort Tea]

718
00:47:36,180 --> 00:47:38,500
So, today's your last day off?

719
00:47:38,500 --> 00:47:43,200
Yeah. I'll go to Mi Jeong's and go home together.

720
00:47:43,200 --> 00:47:45,510
You don't have to pick me up later.

721
00:47:45,510 --> 00:47:47,310
Call me if something comes up.

722
00:47:47,310 --> 00:47:52,020
Don't forget to call when you get home, too. Okay?

723
00:47:52,020 --> 00:47:54,580
Okay, don't worry.

724
00:47:56,450 --> 00:48:00,480
Oh, right. I got a tablet at the conference.

725
00:48:00,480 --> 00:48:03,610
I already have one. Do you need one?

726
00:48:04,640 --> 00:48:07,440
Give it to me. Jin Hee needs one.

727
00:48:07,440 --> 00:48:10,310
She only has a laptop because she's not interested in stuff like that.

728
00:48:10,310 --> 00:48:11,510
Really?

729
00:48:11,510 --> 00:48:14,990
But shouldn't you call her and ask?

730
00:48:14,990 --> 00:48:17,040
She might not like it.

731
00:48:18,020 --> 00:48:19,830
Hold on.

732
00:48:26,130 --> 00:48:29,650
How could I take that? I don't want it.

733
00:48:29,650 --> 00:48:32,740
You accepted everything from my old boyfriends.

734
00:48:32,740 --> 00:48:34,730
Why don't you want this one?

735
00:48:34,730 --> 00:48:37,140
Are you discriminating against him?

736
00:48:37,140 --> 00:48:39,290
Why? Again?

737
00:48:41,280 --> 00:48:43,300
What?

738
00:48:43,300 --> 00:48:45,030
Hey, say that again.

739
00:48:45,030 --> 00:48:49,100
I accepted them because I won't ever see those guys again. Once you cut them off, it's over.

740
00:48:49,100 --> 00:48:51,550
But it's not like that with Ahjussi. How could I accept that?

741
00:48:51,550 --> 00:48:54,900
Hey, I'm with that Ahjussi right now.

742
00:48:54,900 --> 00:48:56,350
You said you were going to see Aunt.

743
00:48:56,350 --> 00:48:58,070
He's driving me there right now.

744
00:48:58,070 --> 00:49:01,000
- Am I on speakerphone, by chance?
- Exactly.

745
00:49:01,000 --> 00:49:02,990
Hang up now.

746
00:49:05,520 --> 00:49:06,980
You heard that. Right?

747
00:49:06,980 --> 00:49:10,870
She's refusing so clearly.

748
00:49:12,050 --> 00:49:15,750
Goodness, I got rejected.

749
00:49:24,700 --> 00:49:26,840
Oh, hello, Boss.

750
00:49:26,840 --> 00:49:28,430
Oh, welcome, Ma'am.

751
00:49:28,430 --> 00:49:31,250
- Hey.
- That way, please.

752
00:49:31,250 --> 00:49:33,040
- That way?
- Yes, yes.

753
00:49:33,040 --> 00:49:35,200
Got it.

754
00:49:35,200 --> 00:49:37,850
This is sea breeze mugwort tea. It's apparently great for women.

755
00:49:37,850 --> 00:49:40,410
I got a box for Mom, too.

756
00:49:40,410 --> 00:49:42,270
Wow, who picked this?

757
00:49:42,270 --> 00:49:43,880
It couldn't have been you.

758
00:49:43,880 --> 00:49:45,270
What?

759
00:49:49,180 --> 00:49:51,150
- What is it?
- How about this one?

760
00:49:51,150 --> 00:49:53,570
I heard it's good for women.

761
00:49:53,570 --> 00:49:55,170
Mugwort tea?

762
00:49:59,740 --> 00:50:01,320
You know, the thing is—

763
00:50:01,320 --> 00:50:03,500
It was Jin Hee, wasn't it?

764
00:50:03,500 --> 00:50:07,520
Goodness, there's no way you have a good taste like this.

765
00:50:11,400 --> 00:50:13,220
Mi Jeong, the thing is—

766
00:50:13,220 --> 00:50:15,670
Did you make up with Jin Hee?

767
00:50:16,930 --> 00:50:18,350
Of course, I did.

768
00:50:18,350 --> 00:50:19,620
How?

769
00:50:19,620 --> 00:50:21,940
What did you say? Tell me.

770
00:50:25,130 --> 00:50:26,790
I just said,

771
00:50:26,790 --> 00:50:30,400
"Hey. Apologize. Shit."

772
00:50:31,640 --> 00:50:35,790
I told you to apologize first, didn't I?

773
00:50:35,790 --> 00:50:37,290
I'm her mom, though.

774
00:50:37,290 --> 00:50:39,960
My gosh. When will you grow up?

775
00:50:39,960 --> 00:50:42,690
I'm seriously so frustrated!

776
00:50:42,690 --> 00:50:46,060
Why are you flipping out? I said I apologized.

777
00:50:48,620 --> 00:50:50,530
Seriously.

778
00:51:13,530 --> 00:51:15,650
I'm sorry, Senior.

779
00:51:19,700 --> 00:51:22,500
- Did you cause trouble behind my back again?
- Pardon?

780
00:51:23,170 --> 00:51:25,510
Well, no, no.

781
00:51:27,210 --> 00:51:29,740
I was just drunk.

782
00:51:29,740 --> 00:51:34,420
I didn't remember because Jin Soo took off without telling me.

783
00:51:35,360 --> 00:51:37,070
I sent you a file. Open that first.

784
00:51:37,070 --> 00:51:39,240
Let's talk while looking at it.

785
00:51:43,300 --> 00:51:47,600
He's the suspect in the park murder. Is he the one you saw?

786
00:51:57,440 --> 00:51:59,350
Mom!

787
00:52:13,140 --> 00:52:16,670
Yes, I think so.

788
00:52:18,000 --> 00:52:19,580
First of all,

789
00:52:20,200 --> 00:52:21,990
let's request witness protection for your mother first.

790
00:52:21,990 --> 00:52:24,060
Hold on.

791
00:52:24,060 --> 00:52:27,550
That means I'll have to expose my mom.

792
00:52:28,200 --> 00:52:30,850
Wouldn't she be in greater danger, then?

793
00:52:30,850 --> 00:52:34,250
Ms. Lee Na Kyeong ended up that way while under witness protection, too.

794
00:52:34,250 --> 00:52:35,770
There's always an exception.

795
00:52:35,770 --> 00:52:39,480
We're requesting witness protection to reduce the chance.

796
00:52:40,530 --> 00:52:42,460
I just...

797
00:52:43,040 --> 00:52:47,800
want you to trust me and rest easy.

798
00:52:47,800 --> 00:52:50,640
And if necessary,

799
00:52:50,640 --> 00:52:56,490
I'll make sure to protect her even if I have to risk my life.

800
00:52:56,490 --> 00:52:58,170
No.

801
00:52:58,170 --> 00:53:00,310
I won't expose her.

802
00:53:01,110 --> 00:53:03,750
Someone is always by her side right now.

803
00:53:03,750 --> 00:53:06,870
And she has me, too.

804
00:53:11,820 --> 00:53:13,310
Let's do this, then.

805
00:53:13,310 --> 00:53:17,180
I'll meet your mother tomorrow.

806
00:53:17,180 --> 00:53:21,270
I'll ask her what she thinks and let her decide.

807
00:53:21,270 --> 00:53:22,970
What do you think?

808
00:53:27,150 --> 00:53:29,690
I don't think that's a good idea, either.

809
00:53:29,690 --> 00:53:32,570
If we tell her that directly...

810
00:53:34,680 --> 00:53:39,360
Senior, I'll keep things this way for now.

811
00:53:45,130 --> 00:53:48,530
You were being considerate. I'm sorry.

812
00:53:48,530 --> 00:53:52,830
It's not like I don't trust you. You know that. Right?

813
00:53:54,950 --> 00:53:57,020
Do you want some beer?

814
00:53:57,890 --> 00:54:01,720
I'm sorry, I drank until I almost puked in Yeosu.

815
00:54:01,720 --> 00:54:04,450
Even Jin Soo said he hasn't seen me that drunk in a long time.

816
00:54:04,450 --> 00:54:06,710
That I was so wasted.

817
00:54:08,310 --> 00:54:12,540
Why did he go on a trip with you and run away?

818
00:54:12,540 --> 00:54:17,080
Oh, he went there for work. He wasn't on the trip.

819
00:54:17,780 --> 00:54:18,720
He went there for work?

820
00:54:18,720 --> 00:54:22,960
Yes, I went on a trip with Mom.

821
00:54:23,950 --> 00:54:27,130
Why did he talk like that, then?

822
00:54:27,800 --> 00:54:30,270
Like "that"? What did he say?

823
00:54:30,270 --> 00:54:32,370
He asked if you'd shower—

824
00:54:33,300 --> 00:54:35,940
- Never mind.
- Pardon?

825
00:54:37,590 --> 00:54:39,480
Senior!

826
00:54:39,480 --> 00:54:41,380
Are you okay?

827
00:54:42,370 --> 00:54:44,710
Senior! Wait for me!

828
00:54:44,710 --> 00:54:46,660
Leave! Leave!

829
00:54:46,660 --> 00:54:47,980
Are you embarrassed?

830
00:54:47,980 --> 00:54:51,360
Isn't that Jin Hee and the Police Academy Oppa?

831
00:54:51,360 --> 00:54:54,020
- Just leave!
- Are you all right?

832
00:54:54,020 --> 00:54:58,210
Isn't that Chief Eun a foolish type, too?

833
00:54:58,210 --> 00:55:00,710
What do you mean, "too"? Is there another fool like him?

834
00:55:00,710 --> 00:55:02,140
I confirmed in Yeosu.

835
00:55:02,140 --> 00:55:04,620
Park Jin Hong is the fool to end all fools.

836
00:55:04,620 --> 00:55:08,830
He proved that so diligently for three days.

837
00:55:11,770 --> 00:55:13,310
You...

838
00:55:13,310 --> 00:55:15,540
You!

839
00:55:15,540 --> 00:55:20,150
Mi Jeong, hey. I was really going to tell you, but...

840
00:55:23,040 --> 00:55:24,820
I'll try dating him!

841
00:55:24,820 --> 00:55:26,690
I'll be in a relationship with him!

842
00:55:26,690 --> 00:55:29,450
Jin Hee said she doesn't care, either.

843
00:55:30,730 --> 00:55:33,400
Mi Jeong!

844
00:55:34,060 --> 00:55:36,860
Just cut me some slack!

845
00:55:36,860 --> 00:55:40,170
Let me date someone like I used to.

846
00:55:40,940 --> 00:55:42,640
Let go.

847
00:55:45,200 --> 00:55:47,540
Hey, Kim Mi Jeong!

848
00:55:48,280 --> 00:55:50,410
Hey! You...

849
00:56:17,870 --> 00:56:20,490
Hey, I'm on my way home.

850
00:56:20,490 --> 00:56:22,710
Goodness, you shouldn't have had a fight.

851
00:56:22,710 --> 00:56:24,680
Where are you? I'll be right there.

852
00:56:24,680 --> 00:56:26,330
It's okay. I'm almost home.

853
00:56:26,330 --> 00:56:28,510
Let's keep talking on the phone until you get home.

854
00:56:28,510 --> 00:56:30,700
It's okay.

855
00:56:30,700 --> 00:56:32,540
I'm really right around the corner.

856
00:56:32,540 --> 00:56:34,080
Let's hang up, Oppa.

857
00:56:34,080 --> 00:56:35,850
I'll call you after I shower when I get home.

858
00:56:35,850 --> 00:56:37,530
Do you want to?

859
00:56:37,530 --> 00:56:40,590
Take a shower quickly and call me, then.

860
00:57:09,650 --> 00:57:12,250
[Daughter]

861
00:57:22,980 --> 00:57:26,520
[Mom]

862
00:57:33,600 --> 00:57:35,380
Excuse me!

863
00:57:36,980 --> 00:57:38,570
Hey!

864
00:58:01,720 --> 00:58:04,850
[112]
(Number for police in Korea)

865
00:58:33,630 --> 00:58:35,530
♫ Want to be free ♫

866
00:58:35,530 --> 00:58:41,340
♫ I want to imagine my life without you ♫

867
00:58:41,340 --> 00:58:44,300
[Not Others]

868
00:58:44,300 --> 00:58:46,360
You said you'd risk your life to protect her.

869
00:58:46,360 --> 00:58:47,920
You said that to me, didn't you?

870
00:58:47,920 --> 00:58:51,460
Do you think I was in danger because he couldn't protect me?

871
00:58:51,460 --> 00:58:53,730
Just focus on the fact that your mom is safe.

872
00:58:53,730 --> 00:58:57,400
Why do you make the ones who like you worry?

873
00:58:57,400 --> 00:58:58,740
You're wearing the same outfit as yesterday.

874
00:58:58,740 --> 00:59:00,080
I couldn't go home last night because I was so drunk.

875
00:59:00,080 --> 00:59:01,560
He can't be married. Right?

876
00:59:01,560 --> 00:59:03,610
Fine. Let's go ahead and do as we'd like.

877
00:59:03,610 --> 00:59:06,500
The culprit. Do you remember how tall he was?

878
00:59:06,500 --> 00:59:08,930
The suspect of the park murder changed his testimony.

879
00:59:08,930 --> 00:59:10,560
That means the real culprit is still out there.

880
00:59:10,560 --> 00:59:12,440
What's with this case, anyway?

881
00:59:12,440 --> 00:59:17,030
♫ You can't cut it off. I know everything ♫
